cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.DM, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with the use of space-filling curves for organising points in the plane into bounding-box hierarchies, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also develops measures of bounding-box quality and locality, which are related to data structures and databases, respectively. Hence, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases) are also likely sub-categories. The paper uses mathematical analysis and algorithms to approximate quality measures, which suggests that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also possible sub-categories.
